1
00:00:01,200 --> 00:00:02,333
<i>Uncle Andy can't be
a partner or an investor.</i>

2
00:00:02,467 --> 00:00:04,500
<i>They just don't want
to be a part of the hotel.</i>

3
00:00:04,633 --> 00:00:06,833
<i>There's something they want
to find or take from me.</i>

4
00:00:06,967 --> 00:00:09,400
<i>Or it could be
at Hotel 88.</i>

5
00:00:09,533 --> 00:00:11,200
<i>You want us to
trust your decision,</i>

6
00:00:11,333 --> 00:00:12,900
<i>but you're not
telling us the truth!</i>

7
00:00:13,033 --> 00:00:14,967
<i>Uncle Andy won't be good
for the hotel.</i>

8
00:00:15,100 --> 00:00:16,133
<i> That's it!</i>

9
00:00:16,267 --> 00:00:17,700
<i>What did you do
to the Almazans, Dad?</i>

10
00:00:17,833 --> 00:00:20,900
They're the ones who rejected us
<i> even if I didn't do anything.</i>

11
00:00:21,033 --> 00:00:21,967
[SCREAMS] Aah!

12
00:00:22,100 --> 00:00:23,100
<i> Jade, what's wrong?!</i>

13
00:00:23,233 --> 00:00:24,333
<i> Kiko, there's a dead person!</i>

14
00:00:24,467 --> 00:00:26,733
<i>We all know that Montevilla
had a lot of enemies.</i>

15
00:00:26,867 --> 00:00:27,800
<i> But what do you think?</i>

16
00:00:27,933 --> 00:00:28,700
<i> It's simple.</i>

17
00:00:28,833 --> 00:00:30,633
<i> Whoever he last fought with.</i>

18
00:00:30,767 --> 00:00:33,100
<i>We would like
to invite Justin and Luna</i>

19
00:00:33,233 --> 00:00:34,833
<i>to talk about the death
of Mr. Peter Montevilla.</i>

20
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:36,167
<i> I'll go.</i>

21
00:00:37,667 --> 00:00:38,600
<i> I'll go too.</i>

22
00:00:46,767 --> 00:00:53,367
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

23
00:00:53,500 --> 00:00:54,367
Hey.

24
00:00:55,767 --> 00:00:57,233
Are you sure you're okay?

25
00:00:58,033 --> 00:00:59,500
Trixie...

26
00:00:59,633 --> 00:01:01,700
[TRIXIE] Duh? Of course,
I'm worried about you.

27
00:01:02,700 --> 00:01:04,400
I'm fine, Trixie.

28
00:01:04,533 --> 00:01:06,833
There's just so much
to take care of.

29
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:09,533
Then let me help you
while Luna's away.

30
00:01:09,667 --> 00:01:10,733
Come on.

31
00:01:11,700 --> 00:01:14,533
Fine. If that can
put your mind at ease.

32
00:01:16,767 --> 00:01:18,800
- Okay. What--
- Good morning, Mr. Madrigal.

33
00:01:19,833 --> 00:01:20,633
Ma'am.

34
00:01:20,767 --> 00:01:22,533
Is there anything else
you need from us?

35
00:01:22,667 --> 00:01:24,633
We've already given
our statements.

36
00:01:25,800 --> 00:01:28,567
We'd like to invite
Mr. Gio Cabrera to the precinct.

37
00:01:31,567 --> 00:01:32,733
Gio?

38
00:01:35,933 --> 00:01:42,733
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

39
00:02:39,967 --> 00:02:42,400
[MONETTE] My bread keeps
disappearing from the pantry.

40
00:02:42,533 --> 00:02:44,100
Have you been eating them?

41
00:02:44,233 --> 00:02:47,467
No way! If I did, I wouldn't
have kept it from you.

42
00:02:47,633 --> 00:02:48,467
Hey.

43
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:52,767
What are you doing in there?

44
00:02:53,833 --> 00:02:56,767
If our food becomes bland,
it'll be your fault.

45
00:02:56,900 --> 00:02:59,900
Then we can just buy
a new one at the market.

46
00:03:00,033 --> 00:03:03,133
I feel like this is the only way

47
00:03:03,267 --> 00:03:06,400
to get rid of the negative
energy around here.

48
00:03:06,533 --> 00:03:08,567
You know, you've been
hanging out with Sari so much

49
00:03:08,700 --> 00:03:10,300
that you're starting
to act like her.

50
00:03:10,433 --> 00:03:13,800
Not all hotels have had
a guest die.

51
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:16,433
But it's not the hotel's fault.

52
00:03:16,567 --> 00:03:18,733
That Peter guy
had a lot of enemies.

53
00:03:19,567 --> 00:03:21,633
In my opinion,
one of them killed him.

54
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:23,967
He had enemies
here on Isla Solara?

55
00:03:24,100 --> 00:03:25,467
Probably.

56
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:27,533
They must've followed him here.

57
00:03:27,667 --> 00:03:30,467
And a lot of tourists
visit the island, right?

58
00:03:30,600 --> 00:03:33,933
But why was Sir Justin
summoned to the precinct

59
00:03:34,067 --> 00:03:36,400
if it was the tourist's fault?

60
00:03:37,633 --> 00:03:38,767
What?

61
00:03:38,900 --> 00:03:40,600
They're suspecting Justin?

62
00:03:40,733 --> 00:03:43,100
- Yes.
- That's what we've heard.

63
00:03:43,233 --> 00:03:46,200
We all know Justin's basically
a regular at the police station.

64
00:03:46,333 --> 00:03:47,900
Maybe they're questioning
everyone.

65
00:03:53,167 --> 00:03:54,900
You're so used to seeing me
at your precinct

66
00:03:55,067 --> 00:03:57,333
whenever the Almazans
get involved in something, huh?

67
00:03:57,467 --> 00:03:59,333
I'm just doing my job.

68
00:04:00,467 --> 00:04:02,200
Are you sure, sir?

69
00:04:02,333 --> 00:04:04,400
Like you said,
we're used to you,

70
00:04:04,533 --> 00:04:06,700
so you can't talk your way
out of this.

71
00:04:07,367 --> 00:04:08,333
Anyway, Chase said--

72
00:04:08,467 --> 00:04:10,233
Yes, I hit that coward!

73
00:04:10,967 --> 00:04:12,767
But I didn't do anything
to that Peter guy.

74
00:04:12,900 --> 00:04:14,167
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

75
00:04:14,300 --> 00:04:16,467
I wish I had faced him
so I could make him pay

76
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:18,367
for what he did to my sister.

77
00:04:18,500 --> 00:04:20,533
But I didn't kill him!

78
00:04:20,667 --> 00:04:23,367
I last saw him when he
caused a scene at the hotel.

79
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:25,333
We reported it to you,
remember?

80
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:30,467
That wasn't the first time
you met him, right?

81
00:04:30,633 --> 00:04:32,400
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

82
00:04:32,533 --> 00:04:33,633
No.

83
00:04:34,867 --> 00:04:36,900
Mr. Montevilla was
facing a lot of cases.

84
00:04:38,267 --> 00:04:40,333
But when he came
to Isla Solara...

85
00:04:41,433 --> 00:04:43,433
something suddenly
happened to him.

86
00:04:45,667 --> 00:04:47,433
And you're saying
it's because of me?

87
00:04:47,567 --> 00:04:49,100
[MARINA]
Are you close with his ex?

88
00:04:49,233 --> 00:04:51,167
Luna Almazan?

89
00:04:51,300 --> 00:04:52,433
Yes.

90
00:04:52,567 --> 00:04:53,733
[MARINA]
And according to reports,

91
00:04:53,867 --> 00:04:56,200
you fought with him when he
caused a scene at the hotel.

92
00:04:56,333 --> 00:04:57,400
Yes, because I was
defending Luna.

93
00:04:57,533 --> 00:04:59,333
So you retaliated?!

94
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:01,733
What?

95
00:05:01,867 --> 00:05:04,867
[MARINA] You got hit many times
by Montevilla.

96
00:05:06,133 --> 00:05:07,567
So you retaliated.

97
00:05:08,900 --> 00:05:10,900
You have a motive.

98
00:05:11,033 --> 00:05:13,500
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

99
00:05:13,633 --> 00:05:14,733
If I wanted to kill Peter,

100
00:05:14,867 --> 00:05:17,133
I would have done it
a long time ago.

101
00:05:17,267 --> 00:05:19,733
I wouldn't let that demon
hurt Luna.

102
00:05:21,233 --> 00:05:22,233
[HENRI] Ms. Almazan,

103
00:05:22,367 --> 00:05:25,300
when was the last time you saw
Peter Montevilla?

104
00:05:25,433 --> 00:05:27,500
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

105
00:05:27,633 --> 00:05:28,800
When...

106
00:05:30,667 --> 00:05:32,867
when he tried to abduct me
from the hotel.

107
00:05:34,067 --> 00:05:36,433
It was that incident we
reported to you the other day.

108
00:05:37,533 --> 00:05:39,633
Are you sure?

109
00:05:39,767 --> 00:05:41,967
Because out of all the people
on this island,

110
00:05:42,100 --> 00:05:45,300
you were the one he was
closest to as his ex-girlfriend.

111
00:05:46,267 --> 00:05:47,600
[HENRI] After what he did
to you, you're--

112
00:05:47,733 --> 00:05:48,733
Sir.

113
00:05:48,867 --> 00:05:49,900
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

114
00:05:50,033 --> 00:05:51,767
He went to the hotel.

115
00:05:51,900 --> 00:05:54,000
I cut off ties with him
a long time ago.

116
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:58,200
- But that doesn't mean--
- That I couldn't kill him?

117
00:05:58,333 --> 00:06:00,833
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

118
00:06:00,967 --> 00:06:03,667
Sir, I cut off ties with him
a long time ago.

119
00:06:04,467 --> 00:06:07,967
If I could forget him, I would.

120
00:06:08,867 --> 00:06:10,600
He was the one
who went to the hotel.

121
00:06:10,733 --> 00:06:13,200
He was the one who did
something bad to me.

122
00:06:13,333 --> 00:06:14,567
Not me.

123
00:06:14,700 --> 00:06:20,800
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

124
00:06:23,100 --> 00:06:24,100
Not yet?

125
00:06:24,233 --> 00:06:25,100
Yeah.

126
00:06:25,233 --> 00:06:26,400
[SNIFFS]

127
00:06:27,700 --> 00:06:29,600
- Well?
- How'd it go?

128
00:06:29,733 --> 00:06:31,567
If I had known I'd be
suspected for killing Peter,

129
00:06:31,700 --> 00:06:32,900
I would've did it for real.

130
00:06:33,033 --> 00:06:34,700
Hey!

131
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:37,967
At least I'd have gotten revenge
for everything they did to us.

132
00:06:38,100 --> 00:06:39,200
What if someone hears you?

133
00:06:39,333 --> 00:06:41,333
They might think
you have a motive.

134
00:06:41,500 --> 00:06:43,967
It's because Dela Paz
kept implying that I did it.

135
00:06:44,100 --> 00:06:45,733
[SIGHS] Those are just words.

136
00:06:45,867 --> 00:06:47,833
There is no material evidence
or witness to prove

137
00:06:47,967 --> 00:06:49,567
that you killed him.

138
00:06:50,533 --> 00:06:52,533
I've talked to Atty. De Castro.

139
00:06:52,667 --> 00:06:55,033
He'll be talking to the police
on your behalf after this.

140
00:06:56,267 --> 00:06:58,133
I wonder who really killed him.

141
00:06:58,267 --> 00:07:02,800
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

142
00:07:02,933 --> 00:07:04,600
Grandpa, please!

143
00:07:04,733 --> 00:07:07,733
Maybe you can find out
who killed Peter.

144
00:07:08,833 --> 00:07:09,767
What?

145
00:07:09,900 --> 00:07:14,067
[SARI] Maybe you can find out
who killed Peter.

146
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:20,133
Sari, I won't see any signs
if I hadn't seen the person.

147
00:07:21,233 --> 00:07:24,600
What if we smoke out the room
where he slept?

148
00:07:26,033 --> 00:07:30,833
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

149
00:07:30,967 --> 00:07:32,300
The question is...

150
00:07:32,433 --> 00:07:34,933
would your boss allow me
to do that?

151
00:07:36,133 --> 00:07:40,000
This will help get rid
of the negative energy there.

152
00:07:40,133 --> 00:07:42,933
And it can fix
the hotel's negative image.

153
00:07:43,067 --> 00:07:46,467
Why was the body found
on the hotel's property anyway?

154
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:47,967
[SARI SIGHS]

155
00:07:48,133 --> 00:07:49,633
All I can say is...

156
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:53,733
that man's death had
something to do

157
00:07:54,667 --> 00:07:57,600
with the secret
Hotel 88 is hiding.

158
00:07:57,733 --> 00:07:59,967
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

159
00:08:00,100 --> 00:08:01,133
A secret?

160
00:08:03,333 --> 00:08:05,100
Looks like they're coming back.

161
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:09,000
[SARI] Who's coming back?

162
00:08:09,133 --> 00:08:11,133
Treasure seekers.

163
00:08:15,900 --> 00:08:17,000
Treasure?

164
00:08:17,667 --> 00:08:18,900
[PHONE RINGING]

165
00:08:19,733 --> 00:08:22,000
Oh, crap!
They're looking for me.

166
00:08:22,167 --> 00:08:23,867
I'll go back now, Grandpa!

167
00:08:25,700 --> 00:08:27,733
[SARI] Bye, Grandpa!
I love you so much!

168
00:08:27,867 --> 00:08:34,633
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

169
00:08:34,767 --> 00:08:37,633
Everyone is getting
closer to the truth.

170
00:08:39,100 --> 00:08:42,033
It's only a matter of time
before they find...

171
00:08:43,433 --> 00:08:45,333
the hidden treasure.

172
00:08:45,467 --> 00:08:49,133
[OMINOUS MUSIC SWELLS]

173
00:08:50,100 --> 00:08:54,733
- [MUSIC TURNS DARK]
- [JUAN GRUNTING]

174
00:08:54,900 --> 00:08:58,233
[WHEEZING]

175
00:08:58,367 --> 00:08:59,733
[COUGHS]

176
00:09:00,567 --> 00:09:07,500
[GRUNTING]

177
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:17,133
[GRUNTING CONTINUES]

178
00:09:17,267 --> 00:09:22,067
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

179
00:09:27,433 --> 00:09:34,267
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

180
00:09:38,267 --> 00:09:39,133
[SCREAMING] Aah!

181
00:09:39,267 --> 00:09:45,067
[GRUNTING]

182
00:09:52,167 --> 00:09:53,933
[WHEEZES]

183
00:09:55,167 --> 00:09:57,933
[PANTING]

184
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:00,267
[BANGING ON DOOR]

185
00:10:00,267 --> 00:10:02,233
- [MAN] Hey!
- [GRUNTS]

186
00:10:02,267 --> 00:10:09,167
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [BREATHING HEAVILY]

187
00:10:12,867 --> 00:10:14,233
- [THWACKS]
- [BODY THUDS]

188
00:10:14,233 --> 00:10:17,900
- [JUAN CHOKES]
- [BOTH GRUNTING]

189
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:22,467
- [THWACKS]
- [GROANS IN PAIN]

190
00:10:22,467 --> 00:10:25,467
[PANTING]

191
00:10:25,667 --> 00:10:28,800
[GRUNTS]

192
00:10:28,800 --> 00:10:35,433
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING,
THEN FADES]

193
00:10:36,600 --> 00:10:38,467
- Justin!
- Justin.

194
00:10:38,467 --> 00:10:40,633
Justin, how are you?
They say you'll go to jail?

195
00:10:40,633 --> 00:10:42,267
Cheska, I don't have
anything to do with that.

196
00:10:43,500 --> 00:10:45,500
We're just making sure.

197
00:10:45,500 --> 00:10:49,267
But you... Are you okay?

198
00:10:49,267 --> 00:10:53,933
You know, I'm used to being
blamed, but never for murder.

199
00:10:53,933 --> 00:10:56,367
It's okay.
You're innocent.

200
00:10:57,567 --> 00:10:59,467
Everything's going to be okay.

201
00:10:59,467 --> 00:11:03,467
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

202
00:11:03,467 --> 00:11:04,667
How'd it go?

203
00:11:05,900 --> 00:11:07,933
Well, they wasted time.

204
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:11,900
They won't get anything.

205
00:11:15,233 --> 00:11:17,533
Going back to the hotel?

206
00:11:17,733 --> 00:11:19,600
Come with us.

207
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:20,733
Sure.

208
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:23,300
Let's go.

209
00:11:23,300 --> 00:11:29,967
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

210
00:11:41,800 --> 00:11:43,467
[JUAN GRUNTS]

211
00:11:44,500 --> 00:11:45,900
[FLOOR CREAKS]

212
00:11:45,900 --> 00:11:52,800
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

213
00:12:06,033 --> 00:12:08,933
[GOON 1] Where is Juan?
Go find him.

214
00:12:08,933 --> 00:12:10,833
[GOON 2]
I'll call Andy.

215
00:12:10,833 --> 00:12:16,967
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

216
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:18,433
<i> Andy.</i>

217
00:12:19,533 --> 00:12:21,833
<i> Your dad's been gone.</i>

218
00:12:21,833 --> 00:12:23,433
<i> - Why does Andy hate him?
- Huh?!</i>

219
00:12:23,433 --> 00:12:25,667
<i>He's why you came here...
to Isla Solara.</i>

220
00:12:25,667 --> 00:12:28,600
<i> The treasure!
What do you know about it?</i>

221
00:12:28,600 --> 00:12:30,900
<i> Where is the map?!</i>

222
00:12:30,900 --> 00:12:35,033
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

223
00:12:35,033 --> 00:12:36,600
Andy Arellano.

224
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:42,467
[BOAT ENGINE WHIRRING]

225
00:12:42,467 --> 00:12:46,000
I hope the hotel's image
isn't ruined by this.

226
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:51,400
It's a big property.
We're surrounded by water.

227
00:12:51,433 --> 00:12:54,100
Anyone could get inside.

228
00:12:54,100 --> 00:12:57,033
We need to strengthen
the security.

229
00:12:57,033 --> 00:13:01,567
[BREATHING DEEPLY]

230
00:13:01,567 --> 00:13:04,767
- Luna.
- Luna. What's wrong?

231
00:13:04,767 --> 00:13:06,033
- Luna. Hey...
- Luna.

232
00:13:06,033 --> 00:13:07,700
Luna, what's happening?

233
00:13:07,700 --> 00:13:08,900
- Luna!
- Wait, wait.

234
00:13:08,900 --> 00:13:11,067
- Luna. Luna, it's me.
- Luna. Breathe.

235
00:13:11,067 --> 00:13:12,533
- Breathe, Luna. Breathe.
- Breathe, Luna.

236
00:13:12,533 --> 00:13:15,433
No! No! No! No...

237
00:13:15,433 --> 00:13:17,467
- Wait, wait.
- Luna. Give her space.

238
00:13:17,467 --> 00:13:18,633
Luna, Luna, Luna.

239
00:13:18,633 --> 00:13:21,333
It's me. It's Jade, it's Jade.
Please, Luna, breathe.

240
00:13:21,367 --> 00:13:22,767
Luna, stay with me.

241
00:13:22,767 --> 00:13:24,100
- Breathe slowly. Slowly.
- Luna.

242
00:13:24,100 --> 00:13:25,400
Luna...

243
00:13:25,400 --> 00:13:26,700
- [PETER] I'll kill myself...
- Don't do that!

244
00:13:26,700 --> 00:13:29,067
<i>- Don't do that!
- Luna, I want to kill myself!</i>

245
00:13:29,067 --> 00:13:30,867
[SOBBING LOUDLY]
<i> No, please!</i>

246
00:13:30,867 --> 00:13:32,733
[GUNSHOTS]
<i> I want to kill myself!</i>

247
00:13:32,733 --> 00:13:35,400
<i>What? You're leaving?
Leaving me behind? Huh?</i>

248
00:13:35,400 --> 00:13:38,000
<i> Do you remember that day?
An innocent got hurt.</i>

249
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:39,333
<i> And that's all because of you!</i>

250
00:13:39,333 --> 00:13:42,800
<i>- Help! Fine, it's my fault!
- It's your fault the kid died!</i>

251
00:13:42,800 --> 00:13:45,033
<i> Help! Peter!</i>

252
00:13:45,033 --> 00:13:47,100
<i>Hurry!
And that's all because of you!</i>

253
00:13:47,100 --> 00:13:50,533
<i>With a view like this,
no wonder you left me.</i>

254
00:13:51,733 --> 00:13:53,433
<i> I'm calling you mine.</i>

255
00:13:53,433 --> 00:13:56,100
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING]

256
00:13:58,100 --> 00:14:00,033
[RAPID, SHALLOW BREATHS]

257
00:14:00,033 --> 00:14:01,967
[JADE] Hey...

258
00:14:03,600 --> 00:14:04,967
- Luna? Luna! Luna!
- Luna! Luna!

259
00:14:04,967 --> 00:14:06,500
- Luna! Luna!
- Luna!

260
00:14:06,500 --> 00:14:08,567
I'll take care of her.

261
00:14:08,567 --> 00:14:10,400
Luna...

262
00:14:16,633 --> 00:14:18,100
[DOOR CLOSES]

263
00:14:26,467 --> 00:14:30,000
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

264
00:14:39,500 --> 00:14:40,933
[PHONE CHIMES]

265
00:14:40,933 --> 00:14:44,733
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

266
00:14:44,733 --> 00:14:46,667
- "Let's meet."
- [JUAN] We need to talk.

267
00:14:49,633 --> 00:14:51,667
Justin, are you alright?

268
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:55,733
Uh. It's nothing.

269
00:14:56,967 --> 00:15:00,400
My friend messaged me.
He invited me over.

270
00:15:02,467 --> 00:15:05,200
You'd go there instead
of checking on your sister?

271
00:15:06,933 --> 00:15:10,200
Well, you're here.
So, you'll handle it?

272
00:15:11,600 --> 00:15:12,633
Justin.

273
00:15:17,833 --> 00:15:21,100
- Luna, wait! Wait!
- I can't anymore...

274
00:15:21,100 --> 00:15:23,000
- I can't take this. I can't.
- Wait, wait, wait, wait.

275
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:25,100
- Make it stop.
- Wait, wait.

276
00:15:25,100 --> 00:15:27,967
- [SOBBING LOUDLY]
- Luna. Luna.

277
00:15:27,967 --> 00:15:30,733
- Luna, I'm here. Luna...
- I just can't anymore.

278
00:15:30,733 --> 00:15:32,800
He died because of me.

279
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:34,833
- That's not true.
- But he's here for me.

280
00:15:34,867 --> 00:15:36,867
He's here because of me.
If he didn't follow me,

281
00:15:36,867 --> 00:15:39,933
- he wouldn't have died.
- You don't know that.

282
00:15:39,933 --> 00:15:44,500
Okay? You can't control
Peter's life or death, Luna.

283
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:46,800
But everyone around me
is getting hurt.

284
00:15:46,800 --> 00:15:48,600
They're hurting, Gio.

285
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:50,500
[SNIFFLING]

286
00:15:50,500 --> 00:15:53,200
No. No.

287
00:15:55,100 --> 00:15:57,267
That's not true, okay?

288
00:15:57,267 --> 00:15:58,700
[SNIFFLES]

289
00:15:58,700 --> 00:15:59,833
No.

290
00:16:01,600 --> 00:16:02,733
No.

291
00:16:04,967 --> 00:16:06,233
Come with me.

292
00:16:06,233 --> 00:16:10,600
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC PLAYING]

293
00:16:10,633 --> 00:16:11,933
Come with me.

294
00:16:11,933 --> 00:16:18,800
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC CONTINUES]

295
00:16:30,133 --> 00:16:36,833
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

296
00:16:37,933 --> 00:16:39,300
[JUAN] Justin!

297
00:16:39,300 --> 00:16:42,633
[COUGHING, GROANING]

298
00:16:44,767 --> 00:16:46,167
Let's talk.

299
00:16:47,633 --> 00:16:49,767
Not here. Let's go.

300
00:16:51,633 --> 00:16:52,833
[COUGHS]

301
00:16:57,933 --> 00:16:59,567
- Bro.
- What?

302
00:17:00,733 --> 00:17:02,633
Trixie and I
are just going to go somewhere.

303
00:17:03,633 --> 00:17:07,100
There's... There's something we
have to take care of at the bar.

304
00:17:08,767 --> 00:17:11,333
Okay. Be careful.

305
00:17:11,333 --> 00:17:12,400
Bye.

306
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:16,467
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

307
00:17:16,500 --> 00:17:17,567
What about you, bro?

308
00:17:19,267 --> 00:17:20,500
I'll wait for Luna at the hotel.

309
00:17:22,100 --> 00:17:23,233
Okay.

310
00:17:23,233 --> 00:17:25,100
I'm sure Gio will keep her safe.

311
00:17:25,100 --> 00:17:26,100
Jade.

312
00:17:31,167 --> 00:17:32,533
- Edward.
- Are you okay?

313
00:17:32,533 --> 00:17:39,467
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

314
00:17:41,033 --> 00:17:42,133
Let's go.

315
00:17:45,233 --> 00:17:47,067
We're going back to the hotel.

316
00:17:49,433 --> 00:17:50,433
I'll join you.

317
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:52,400
Is that okay?

318
00:18:07,567 --> 00:18:09,567
[SLAPS] Stupid!

319
00:18:10,300 --> 00:18:12,233
He hasn't gone far
from the island.

320
00:18:12,233 --> 00:18:14,433
Don't come back here
until you have Juan!

321
00:18:14,433 --> 00:18:15,667
- Go!
- Yes, sir.

322
00:18:15,667 --> 00:18:16,833
Find him!

323
00:18:16,833 --> 00:18:21,633
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

324
00:18:33,333 --> 00:18:34,700
- Thanks, boss.
- Thank you, sir.

325
00:18:36,633 --> 00:18:37,767
Come.

326
00:18:37,767 --> 00:18:44,700
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

327
00:18:57,367 --> 00:18:58,733
[CHUCKLES] The lights turned on.

328
00:19:00,367 --> 00:19:02,133
- It's been so long since--
- I know.

329
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:11,700
This is what you do
when you want to breathe...

330
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:16,433
when the world
is too complicated.

331
00:19:19,333 --> 00:19:20,333
Let's do one song?

332
00:19:21,800 --> 00:19:22,767
Let's go.

333
00:19:22,767 --> 00:19:29,733
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

334
00:19:43,633 --> 00:19:50,567
[CLUB MUSIC PLAYING]

335
00:20:05,600 --> 00:20:12,500
[CLUB MUSIC CONTINUES]

336
00:20:19,367 --> 00:20:26,333
["TADHANA" BY SOFRONIO VASQUEZ
PLAYING]

337
00:20:32,800 --> 00:20:39,533
[CROWD CHEERING, CLAPPING]

338
00:20:43,967 --> 00:20:50,967
["TADHANA" CONTINUES]

339
00:21:02,633 --> 00:21:03,800
Thank you, Gio.

340
00:21:04,633 --> 00:21:06,667
I felt like I was able
to breathe again.

341
00:21:13,933 --> 00:21:15,700
Why are you looking at me
like that?

342
00:21:18,833 --> 00:21:20,867
Gio, what's on your mind?

343
00:21:25,667 --> 00:21:28,667
I can't afford
to lose you again.

344
00:21:31,767 --> 00:21:33,967
When I saw you having
a hard time earlier...

345
00:21:38,367 --> 00:21:39,733
I don't know why, but...

346
00:21:40,700 --> 00:21:41,833
it's hard.

347
00:21:44,867 --> 00:21:46,000
It hurts here.

348
00:21:52,800 --> 00:21:54,367
It also felt like...

349
00:21:58,933 --> 00:22:01,567
It felt like I was about
to lose you again.

350
00:22:01,567 --> 00:22:08,567
["TADHANA" INSTRUMENTAL
PLAYING]

351
00:22:16,500 --> 00:22:17,967
I love you, Luna.

352
00:22:22,633 --> 00:22:24,333
I still love you.

353
00:22:29,700 --> 00:22:31,567
That never changed.

354
00:22:35,567 --> 00:22:36,900
Gio, the bridge.

355
00:22:39,767 --> 00:22:41,067
We'll cross the bridge
once we're ready

356
00:22:41,067 --> 00:22:42,667
to accept each other.

357
00:22:47,467 --> 00:22:49,067
I crossed that bridge...

358
00:22:49,800 --> 00:22:51,567
a long time ago.

359
00:22:59,367 --> 00:23:02,767
[SNIFFLES] And I've never left
ever since.

360
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:06,433
I love you, Gio.

361
00:23:09,067 --> 00:23:11,400
And you'll never lose me again.

362
00:23:11,933 --> 00:23:18,933
["TADHANA" BY SOFRONIO VASQUEZ
PLAYING]

363
00:23:19,467 --> 00:23:20,433
[SMOOCHES]

364
00:23:35,500 --> 00:23:42,467
["TADHANA" CONTINUES]

365
00:23:45,267 --> 00:23:48,733
- [OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]
- [ENGINE REVVING]

366
00:23:48,733 --> 00:23:50,933
[HANDBRAKE CLICKS]

367
00:23:50,933 --> 00:23:52,967
[ENGINE STOPS]

368
00:23:52,967 --> 00:23:56,333
[CAR DOORS CLOSE]

369
00:23:56,367 --> 00:23:58,000
- What now?
- What?!

370
00:23:58,000 --> 00:23:59,933
Did you bring me here
to kill me?!

371
00:23:59,933 --> 00:24:02,333
Or are you giving me
back to those bastards?!

372
00:24:02,333 --> 00:24:03,700
What are you talking about?

373
00:24:03,700 --> 00:24:07,067
You had me kidnapped!
You gave the order!

374
00:24:08,667 --> 00:24:11,767
I didn't!
I was looking for you.

375
00:24:11,767 --> 00:24:14,033
I saw them kidnap you
from your dad's house!

376
00:24:14,033 --> 00:24:15,833
Don't play me for a fool!

377
00:24:15,833 --> 00:24:19,333
You're the fool!
Always accusing me!

378
00:24:19,333 --> 00:24:21,300
I told you,
it wasn't me, okay?

379
00:24:23,500 --> 00:24:28,533
You know, if you don't trust
me, I'll just leave you here.

380
00:24:28,567 --> 00:24:31,033
I'm wasting my time on you.

381
00:24:31,033 --> 00:24:33,067
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

382
00:24:33,067 --> 00:24:34,567
Wait!

383
00:24:37,500 --> 00:24:39,367
- Andy.
- [CAR DOOR CLOSES]

384
00:24:40,533 --> 00:24:42,100
Do you know an Andy?

385
00:24:45,433 --> 00:24:46,867
Sir Andy.

386
00:24:48,400 --> 00:24:51,933
That's what they call him.
That's what I heard.

387
00:24:54,700 --> 00:24:56,333
I know one Andy.

388
00:24:57,467 --> 00:24:59,700
Andy Arellano?

389
00:24:59,700 --> 00:25:01,067
That's my hunch, too.

390
00:25:01,067 --> 00:25:04,033
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

391
00:25:04,067 --> 00:25:06,700
He's the one
behind your kidnapping?

392
00:25:06,700 --> 00:25:08,533
How do you know Uncle Andy?

393
00:25:08,533 --> 00:25:13,767
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

394
00:25:13,767 --> 00:25:15,800
I don't know him.

395
00:25:15,800 --> 00:25:18,067
Papa mentioned him
to me a long time ago.

396
00:25:20,133 --> 00:25:21,433
Wait.

397
00:25:22,467 --> 00:25:25,167
H-How? W-Why?

398
00:25:25,167 --> 00:25:28,533
What does he know?
Why did he kidnap you?

399
00:25:28,533 --> 00:25:30,833
They're looking
for Papa through me.

400
00:25:30,833 --> 00:25:34,867
And like us, they are
after the treasure.

401
00:25:38,033 --> 00:25:40,000
Treasure?

402
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:43,433
Juan, are you
messing with me now?

403
00:25:43,433 --> 00:25:46,167
There's treasure buried
at Hotel 88.

404
00:25:46,167 --> 00:25:51,867
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

405
00:25:53,567 --> 00:25:55,700
<i>I know why you don't want
Uncle Andy as a partner.</i>

406
00:25:55,700 --> 00:25:57,800
<i>It has something
to do with Sandro Soliman.</i>

407
00:25:57,800 --> 00:26:00,667
<i>I told you, never say
that name again.</i>

408
00:26:00,667 --> 00:26:02,800
<i>Talk to me or I'll
shout his name out?!</i>

409
00:26:02,800 --> 00:26:05,033
<i> - What the hell, Justin?!
- Maybe...</i>

410
00:26:05,033 --> 00:26:07,667
<i> you shouldn't
come here for now?</i>

411
00:26:07,667 --> 00:26:10,167
<i> You are no longer an asset.</i>

412
00:26:10,200 --> 00:26:11,900
<i> You are a liability.</i>

413
00:26:11,900 --> 00:26:14,567
<i>Make sure you get
out of there alive, alright?</i>

414
00:26:16,033 --> 00:26:18,700
<i>And I believe it was
Andy Arellano.</i>

415
00:26:18,700 --> 00:26:22,633
<i>We need to remove all
your tracks here. Clean it up!</i>
